bio: All the news and information you need to see, curated by the @ABCNews team.

posts.description:
Loyola-Chicago has a big fan on their sideline: Sister Jean Dolores Schmidt, the 98-year-old team chaplain.

She not only prays with the team before games, but gives scouting reports afterward. (AP Photo/Tony Gutierrez)
Watch Victoria, a 10-year-old puppy mill survivor, learn how to play with a toy for the first time.
Bring It On: Adorable baby who has undergone three surgeries flexes a muscle to show he's a fighter.
Hundreds of thousands on hand to greet Pope Francis as he arrives for his first Mass in Myanmar.
This thirsty koala graciously accepted some help from human friends as scorching heatwave hits Australia.
93-year-old actress Eva Marie Saint: "I just realized something: I'm older than the Academy."

The 50th annual Iditarod kicked off its ceremonial start in Anchorage, with fans lining up to cheer on the teams, and one second sled driver taking a tumble on a turn. He gets right back up on the sled!
Emma Gonzalez stayed on stage at the D.C.
TO THE RESCUE: Stranger helps a driver escape to safety after rushing floodwaters swept his car away in Canyon Country, California, flipping the vehicle upside down.
"I owe this, and so much more, to so many." Gary Oldman accepts the Academy Award for Best Actor.
Small plane makes hard landing at San Antonio Airport, appearing to skid on its belly for about 100 yards before coming to a stop. No injures reported.
BREAKING: Former first lady Barbara Bush has died at age 92, family spokesperson says.
Karamel the squirrel lost his front paws when he got caught in a trap. Now he’s got a fancy new set of wheels to help him get around.
Thousands of people filled one of Istanbul's busiest streets for
Bystander video shows large police and fire response outside Port Authority Bus Terminal in NYC.
15 years ago today, a statue of longtime Iraqi leader Saddam Hussein was toppled in downtown Baghdad.
Mesmerizing holiday lights display at the iconic Saks Fifth Avenue store in New York City.
Two bear cubs rescued after their mom was struck and killed by a car are gaining weight and on the road to recovery, playing with two other rescued cubs at a wildlife shelter in Virginia.
Rescuers work tirelessly to free horses trapped in burning barns amid devastating wildfires in Southern California.
Hawaii tests nuclear warning system for the first time since the Cold War amid heightened tensions with North Korea.
Scientists discover 170-million-year-old sauropod footprints that reveal insight into how different dinosaurs may have evolved.
Adorable baby tigers spend a glorious Friday frolicking and playing. Enjoy the weekend!

NASA transforms selfies taken by its Mars rover Curiosity into a stunning self-portrait.
Dozens of pictures, taken by the self-focusing camera on the end of Curiosity's arm, were used to create the mosaic.
Staff, students and parents of Georgia academy surprise their beloved maintenance man with a brand new riding lawnmower for his home: "They really touched my heart."
Pregnant woman reportedly fined for deliberately tripping 4-year-old boy at restaurant in northern China.

FREE CAR WASH: A police officer dispatched to check out a reported goat in the road arrived to find the goat in question – along seven with 7 of his friends that escaped from their enclosure. The entire group seems to have a taste for salt.
Curious beachgoer discovers blanket of snow hiding underneath the sand after the latest blast of wintry weather hit the UK.

A bus driver in New Jersey is seen to have run through caution tape condoning off a street, and dangerously using traffic cones to move downed power lines after a nor’easter brought heavy snow and wind to the area.
FINAL FAREWELL: Police officers line the streets and salute processional carrying Chicago Police Commander Paul Bauer, who was killed in the line of duty.
Surveillance video captures three men allegedly stealing $125,000 worth of bicycles at a bike shop in the Netherlands.
Incredible video shows a 40-year old University of Texas building being imploded in Austin, sending plumes of smoke billowing above the city.
Tokyo’s Ueno Zoo celebrates the upcoming debut of panda cub Xiang Xiang, who will begin appearing before the public on Tuesday.
Princes William and Harry greeted by BB-8 and stormtroopers as they walk the red carpet for the European premiere of 'Star Wars: The Last Jedi.'
Pulp Fiction: Police in Spain arrest five people for the theft of almost 9,000 pounds of oranges.
Bathroom at an Arizona aquarium named “Best Restroom in America” thanks to its unobstructed view of the shark tank.
Watching zookeepers in Prague use a puppet to feed an endangered baby Javan green magpie will make your entire day.
LUCKY ESCAPE: Dramatic police dash cam footage captures the moment officers rescue a man from a house fire, seconds before the building explodes. One person was treated for burns, police said.
This adorable 5-year-old boy called 911 to stop the Grinch from stealing Christmas: "I just want to tell you something. Watch for that little Grinch. Because the Grinch is gonna steal Christmas."
New York City Police Department truck catches fire after breaking down at a major intersection, sending flames and black smoke billowing over the heart of the city.
“Fix Fakebook” cutouts of Mark Zuckerberg stand in front of U.S. Capitol ahead of the Facebook CEO’s data privacy testimony in front of Congress today.
Pope Francis brought his motorcade to a halt to help a police officer who fell off his horse while riding alongside their route, staying until an ambulance arrived.
@jimmykimmel makes emotional return to @jimmykimmellive with his son Billy by his side: “I was out last week because this guy had heart surgery, but look, he’s fine everybody!”
Fire caused by a live wire downed in a snowstorm burns in Bridgewater, New Jersey; the storm left almost 1 million without power.
Prince William leaves hospital after he and Princess Kate welcomed a baby boy this morning.
Not worth it: Fisherman loses his catch to a crocodile in Australia's East Alligator River.
Timelapse shows crews transforming Hollywood's Dolby Theatre to prepare for the
Europe's first "selfieccino" cafe opens in London, allowing patrons to print their faces on their hot, frothy beverages.

Sen. Jeff Flake warns against "adding deafness to our already stunning blindness." "In the sweep of our history, we have never been urged to not listen to what a president says. Such admonitions are preposterous now."
Jeb Bush: "What I love about my mom was the fact that she was our first teacher."
Barack Obama praises Michelle Obama's portraitist "for so spectacularly capturing the grace and beauty and intelligence and charm—and hotness—of the woman I love."
Incredible timelapse video captures cold front rolling into New Orleans on Tuesday morning.
Cosby accusers in tears outside courtroom after Bill Cosby is found guilty on all counts in sexual assault retrial.
Footage shows buildings missing their facades and rubble in the streets of Sarpol-e Zahab, near the Iran-Iraq border, after powerful earthquake kills more than 400 people.

Frigid temperatures cause Minnehaha Falls waterfall in Minnesota to freeze. Adventure seekers are braving the slick surfaces to get behind the falls, which park officials say is not only unsafe, but illegal.
Pres. Trump on consulting with Secretary of State Tillerson on his decision to talk with North Korea: “I really didn’t discuss it very much with him, honestly.”
Pres. Trump and Melania Trump were joined by the Easter Bunny this morning to kick off the annual White House Easter Egg Roll.
Video shows fishermen jumping off a sinking boat to a waiting U.S. Coast Guard vessel sent to rescue them.
Heavy winds and snow rip through East Coast from Virginia to New Jersey as snowy "bomb cyclone" bears down.
A blanket of snow covers Rome and its famous monuments, turning the Italian capital into a winter wonderland. It's the first snowfall in the city in six years.
Young Mason wanted a toy from the claw machine so badly, he crawled up into the machine to get it. Thankfully, he wasn’t injured, and he went home with a stuffed toy.
Stunning images capture tiny bioluminescent phytoplankton lighting up the California coast earlier this week.
Stunning video from the front lines captures firefighters battling Southern California wildfires.
A 1952 Mickey Mantle baseball card in mint condition sold for $2.88 million — making it the second-highest price ever paid for a baseball card. In 1988, the card could be had for $3,300.
Police in Australia intercept yacht from alleged drug smuggling syndicate filled with $186 million of cocaine.
Disturbing bodycam footage shows a police officer initiating an "unnecessary physical confrontation" with a woman before ordering a rookie officer to tase her. The officer has since been fired.
DHS Sec. Nielsen says replacing current sections of border wall would count as "new wall": "To us, it's all new wall...This is the Trump border wall."
Police release video of an officer slipping on snow while checking on an abandoned vehicle to "highlight the dangers officers can face" daily.
First ladies Melania Trump and Brigitte Macron ditched the White House today for a visit with the works of Paul Cezanne at the National Gallery of Art in Washington, D.C. (Getty/AFP/AP Photo)
Former VP Joe Biden is celebrating his 75th birthday today. Happy birthday, Joe!
TO THE RESCUE: A woman bravely wades through freezing water to rescue a dog that fell through thin ice.
Prince William and Kate, Duchess of Cambridge, play bandy, a forerunner to ice hockey, on their first visit to Sweden. Princess Kate nails the shot!
This incredible polar bear needs nothing more than a simple toy to keep her occupied all day long.
Photos show inside the Florida high school as students shelter during school shooting.

Powerful winds in Southern California made a wildfire explode to nearly 4 square miles just hours after it broke out Monday night, forcing the evacuation of more than 400 homes, Ventura County fire officials say. Thomas Aquinas College, a school with about 350 students, was also evacuated. The National Weather Service says gusts over 60 mph have been reported in the area.
CLOSE CALL: Quick-thinking bus driver saves 15 passengers from being crushed by massive boulders during a landslide.
Lin-Manuel Miranda encourages viewers to visit Puerto Rico after devastating hurricane: “Keep Puerto Rico in the conversation...keep Puerto Rico in your hearts.”
Two teenagers make the most out of the severe weather in France, cruising down the flooded streets and doing tricks on their wakeboards.
Pres. Trump launched his planned 2020 election campaign slogan at a weekend rally in Pennsylvania: "Keep America Great!"
Rocco the dog uses his tail to lure the reluctant Chester the kitten to play with him. Now they're best friends.
RIP, Billy Graham. One of the world's most famous Christian evangelists has died at age 99.
Massive celebration breaks out in the streets of Tuscaloosa, Alabama, after Alabama wins the college football national championship.

Broward County Sheriff Scott Israel visits 15-year-old Anthony Borges, who is recovering in the hospital after being shot several times while protecting his classmates during the deadly school shooting Wednesday.

Speaking at the McConnell Center, Sen. Chuck Schumer presents Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell with a bottle of Brooklyn bourbon. "There's no such thing as Brooklyn bourbon," the Kentucky senator responded.
On its first flight of the new year, SpaceX launches secret satellite codenamed Zuma from Cape Canaveral in Florida.
Four agencies team up to rescue a dog that chased a cat into a 5-foot deep hole dug by a tortoise.
The annual four-day Crufts dog show sees around 22,000 pedigree dogs visit the NEC Arena in Birmingham, England, before the "Best in Show" is awarded on the final day.
At least 1,000 people gathered in Parkland, Florida on Thursday night for a candlelight vigil dedicated to the 17 people killed in the shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School. 📷: Getty
This 5-year-old boy only wanted one thing for his birthday: “I wish I could be a UPS driver.” What happened next will leave you smiling.
Jaw-dropping dash cam video shows a driver losing control and driving over a parked car.
“What did you do?” This adorable toddler used his Hot Wheels to lead his dad on a scavenger hunt … which unfortunately ended with the rest of his toy cars clogging the toilet.
Frozen: Stunning drone footage captures icy scene at Old Silver Beach in Massachusetts as frigid temperatures grip much of the East Coast.
Dr. Bennet Omalu, pioneer in CTE research, delivers results of his private autopsy of Stephon Clark. “There were a total of 8 gunshot wounds…he received 7 gunshot wounds from his back.”
Watch the reaction of these
Spectacular photos show the super blue blood moon setting before dawn as lava cascades down the slopes of the Philippines’ Mount Mayon volcano during an eruption. (AP)

A rendition of the Canadian National Anthem was sung at the Nashville Predators hockey game on Saturday in honor of the victims in the deadly Humboldt Broncos bus crash in Saskatchewan that left 15 people dead.
BREAKING: The Manhattan offices of Michael Cohen, Donald Trump's longtime personal attorney, were raided today by federal agents.
Tens of thousands of holiday revelers braved freezing temperatures to see fireworks and neon-drenched ice structures at the Harbin Ice and Snow World.
Christmas prank: T-Rex does his best "Grinch" impression, "breaking into" a home and stealing all the Christmas decorations.
Super Bowl MVP Nick Foles brings the Philadelphia Eagles celebration to Main Street USA at Walt Disney World: "To be at Disney World, to be a part of this, it’s unbelievable."

Pope Francis boards a chartered flight to Bangladesh and Myanmar as he heads to the site of one of the world's most intense crises. He’ll arrive Monday in Myanmar where a military crackdown on the country's Muslim Rohingya has caused international outrage. Mass rapes, shootings and the burning of entire villages since the operation began in August have triggered a humanitarian crisis, with 620,000 Rohingya fleeing into neighboring Bangladesh. The situation, which unfolded after the trip was arranged, will now dominate the Pope’s visit and make it possibly the most difficult of his papacy to date. (@jamesaalongman)
A fleet of snow removal vehicles work to clear snow from a runway at Reagan National Airport during the fourth nor'easter to slam the East Coast in recent weeks.
Lawmaker pressures Mark Zuckerberg to improve diversity at Facebook. "This does not represent America...we can do better than that, Mr. Zuckerberg."

Princess Kate left the hospital just seven hours after giving birth to her third child yesterday.

When Kate delivered George in 2013 (first photo), she stayed in the hospital just one night, and in 2015, Kate left St. Mary’s Hospital less than 10 hours after delivering her second child, Charlotte (second photo). AFP/Getty Images
Photos show window blown out on Southwest jet that made emergency landing in Philadelphia. (Marty Martinez/Facebook)
Two American astronauts and a Russian cosmonaut blasted off aboard a rocket early this morning on their way to the International Space Station.

Newly released video shows the moment the rotor blades of two Pasadena police helicopters collided, destroying both aircraft and causing minor injuries to 6 people. The NTSB blamed the collision on rainy weather and a lack of communication between pilots.

Hugs and high-fives for Nancy Pelosi after the House Minority Leader set a record - speaking on the House floor from morning until early evening on immigration and reading letters from DACA recipients.

Prince Harry and Meghan Markle don’t need a new set of dishes, a personalized picture frame, a vase or a stand mixer for their upcoming wedding.

Instead, the couple – whose passion for humanitarian issues reportedly brought them together -- would like donations made to their favorite charities, Kensington Palace announced today.
This might be one of the most epic soccer goals of all time: Kansas high school soccer star Ashlyn delivers a front-flip throw to set up her teammate Rachel to hit a game-winning goal.

Police dogs and their handlers arrive on the scene of the latest explosion in Austin, Texas - just hours after the city's police chief urged the suspect in the recent string of bombings to turn themselves in. Local and federal emergency units responded Sunday night to another explosion in which two more people were injured. A law enforcement source tells ABC News it will take some time to determine whether this latest blast is linked to the earlier bombings. Those bombings killed two people and injured two others.
TO PROTECT AND SERVE: Police officers and firefighters revive a 9-week-old Saint Bernard puppy who was choking on food.
On International Women's Day, NGOs and human rights organizations are taking the opportunity to advocate for equality, fair treatment and progress for women. (FRANCISCO SECO/AP)
Police are looking to identify approximately 20 men involved in a massive bar brawl in Leeds, England, where glasses, tables and chairs were used as weapons.
Cellphone video captures dramatic scene as a member of the Redondo Beach Harbor Patrol jumps into the water to help rescue two sailors and a dog. Luckily, no one was seriously injured.
Forget the players—this grandma's amazing tambourine skills at a Louisiana football game were what won the crowd.
Pres. Trump recognizes

Pres. Trump says he's "not at all concerned" about Attorney General Jeff Sessions' interview with the special counsel team, and disputes reports that FBI Director Chris Wray threatened to resign over pressure to replace top staff.
Spring has finally sprung, and these newborn baby goats are loving it!
KEGS TOSSED: Tractor trailer carrying beer fell from a ramp onto a highway in Bensalem, Pennsylvania, spilling kegs full of beer all over the road. Thankfully, no one was injured.
Pres. Trump signs a hat on the way out of the House chamber after finishing his first State of the Union address. (Win McNamee/Getty Images)
Gorgeous timelapse captures the Leonid meteor shower streaking across the night sky over England.

Sen. Lindsey Graham tells @theviewabc he called Donald Trump a "xenophobic, race-baiting religious bigot," but "he won. Guess what: he's our president...and he's doing a really good job on multiple fronts."
Touching video shows the moment Irgo the German shepherd was finally reunited with his family after United Airlines mistakenly shipped the dog to Japan instead of Kansas City.
The first panda born in France has a special godmother—French first lady Bridgette Macron. She revealed the panda will be named "Yuan Meng," meaning "Dreams Come True."

Dramatic video shows a hot air balloon making an emergency landing in a San Diego neighborhood.

Emergency services and good Samaritans helped to keep the basket steady as the 14 passengers exited safely. No one was injured.
Skier trapped on a stopped ski lift films smoke rising from a volcanic eruption in Kusatsu, Japan, about 100 miles from Tokyo.
The New York Stock Exchange got a little more magical this morning, when Mickey Mouse rang the opening bell.
TIMELESS LOVE: First-time grandmother, living with Alzheimer's, remembers a song from her childhood to sing to her granddaughter.

Two rings of chairs encircle the words “NEVER AGAIN” outside Trinity High School in New Hampshire. The inner ring chairs have the names of Columbine victims, and the outer the names of Parkland shooting victims.

Good Samaritans and rescue workers rush to dig out a man who was completely buried by an avalanche that crashed down on a ski resort in California. Someone spotted the man's snowboard sticking out from the snow, which is credited with saving his life.

Democrat Doug Jones will win the Alabama special election, @ABCNews projects, defeating GOP challenger Roy Moore. Jones told supporters: "We have shown not just around the state of Alabama, but we have shown the country the way – that we can be unified."
SUV slams through a house in California after driver allegedly fell asleep at the wheel. No one was seriously injured, but surveillance footage captured the significant property damage.
“Send them to jail,” Felix Sater tells @gstephanopoulos, when asked his reaction if special counsel Robert Mueller's investigation uncovers collusion between Trump associates and Russia.

The U.S. Navy's newest attack submarine, the USS Colorado, will go into service Saturday at the Naval Submarine Base in Connecticut.
The 377-foot-long sub weighs about 7,800 tons submerged, and has two large tubes that can launch six Tomahawk missiles each. (Sean D. Elliot/The Day via AP)
Dramatic security cam video captures the moment powerful earthquake rocked eastern Taiwan. At least 7 people were killed and dozens have been reported missing.

The powerful National Memorial for Peace and Justice, also referred to as the lynching museum, is set to open in Montgomery, Alabama on Thursday. The Equal Justice Initiative hope the memorial and museum will offer a reflection on America’s history of racial inequality.
UN Amb. Haley: "Did a chemical weapons attack happen? Yes...There is proof that this happened."
The T. Rex may have once been the world's most fearsome predator, but snowboarding appears beyond its skills.
"I can see Fiona!" Fiona the hippo puts on a show for excited zoogoers in Cincinnati.
Good Samaritan wrestles an alligator using a broom and a blanket to remove a plastic ring wrapped around its body.

LOVE AT ANY AGE: Ann and Allen got married this week at the Texas senior living center where they both reside. The couple says they met about two months ago and fell in love “at first sight,” proving that you can find love at any age.
Backstage at the Oscars, Frances McDormand explains how the inclusion rider clause allows actors to "demand at least 50% diversity in not only the casting, but also the crew."
Surveillance video shows robbers disguised as senior citizens steal thousands of dollars in Rolex watches from a Georgia jewelry store.

As more women go into sciences and the media shows them doing so, younger children are getting the message: They are drawing scientists as female more than ever before, a new study shows. (PHOTOS COURTESY LEON WALLS/VASILLA CHRISTIDOU)
Royal wedding DJ? London DJ takes his shot, gives Prince Harry his business card as the newly-engaged couple arrives for an appearance at a youth radio station.
TOUGH LOVE: Adorable baby panda is taught how to toughen up from their mama, as they tussle and tumble around the snow.
President Trump, First Lady Melania Trump light their first National Christmas Tree.
When Simon Beck left his office job to follow his passion for art, he found his perfect fresh start in nature. Now dubbed the world’s first snow artist, Beck creates art on the unconventional canvas.
Asked his biggest military concern of 2018, Defense Sec. James Mattis responds, "I don't have concerns, I create them."

Gold medalist Chloe Kim is attracting fans from around the world—including from South Korea, where her father lived before emigrating to the U.S. in 1982. "It means a lot just being able to do it where my family is from," she says. (Getty/Newscom/AP/Reuters)

NYC animal shelter says puppy believed to be paralyzed after being thrown from a moving car is defying the odds and has started to walk again after undergoing hernia surgery and physical therapy. Good luck, Banky Brewster!
Former Beatles drummer Ringo Starr knighted by Prince William in ceremony at Buckingham Palace. 📸: AP/Getty

SNEAK PEEK: Kensington Palace and The Obama Foundation released a sneak preview of Prince Harry's interview of former Pres. Barack Obama. "You’re excited about this. I’m nervous about this. That’s what’s quite funny." The interview, which will air later this month on the BBC, will touch on their shared interest in building platforms for the next generation of young leaders and Obama's memories of the day he left office.

Pres. Trump at National Prayer Breakfast: "When Americans are able to live by their convictions, to speak openly of their faith, and to teach their children what is right, our families thrive, our communities flourish, and our nation can achieve anything at all."
“This is what Democracy looks like!” Students and allies rally outside of the U.S. Capitol building in Washington, D.C. as part of
Large fire breaks out after a reports of an explosion at a chemical recycling company in Mansfield, Texas. No one was inside the plant, according to fire officials.
Firefighters in Montecito, California rescue a 14-year-old girl trapped inside her house for hours amid flooding and mudslides caused by deadly winter storm.
CATCH A WAVE: Baby marine turtles make their way to the ocean in Melbourne, Florida.
Activists across Iran shared videos of women walking without a hijab or head scarf on
A waste management company in England dumps the contents of a dumpster onto a customer’s front yard after the customer failed to pay for overloading the container.
The dark January streets of London are being transformed into an illuminated outdoor gallery as part of the city's Lumiere arts festival.
Stunned tourists get up close and personal with a pod of minke whales swimming right under their boat in Antarctica.
Children's hospital jumps into action to help save a 7-year-old's Elf on a Shelf after it was attacked by her dog.
WEATHER WARNING: Michigan Sheriff Mike Bouchard is threatening to lock up Mother Nature after the latest spring snowstorm. "It's time to stop this and focus on a little warmth for good old Michigan."
A 60-unit apartment complex in downtown Ventura is among at least 150 structures destroyed by wildfires burning across Southern California. Fire officials said they expect that number could go up.

IF AT FIRST YOU DON'T SUCCEED: This determined little soccer player tries, tries, and tries again when he keeps missing the ball. Isaiah eventually gets his shot away, proving that perseverance pays off.
The American flag hanging outside United States consulate building in St. Petersburg is taken down, following Russia's order to close the embassy and expel 60 U.S. diplomats earlier this week.
Authorities respond to a massive sinkhole that formed on a residential street in Fairfax, Virginia.
Video shows firefighters in Taiwan attempting to get inside collapsed hotel where at least two people were trapped after 6.4-magnitude earthquake.
"Wow!" This toddler couldn't believe his eyes when he saw his first snowfall in Tallahassee, Florida.
Meet Meghan, Zoological Society of London's new okapi, named after Meghan Markle. Researchers estimate there are only 25,000 okapis left in the wild.
JUST IN: President Trump comments after speaking with Florida school shooting victims and doctors who cared for them: "We saw numerous people and incredible recovery."

Police in Denmark investigating after "world’s most expensive bottle of vodka" - worth an estimated $1.3 million - stolen from Copenhagen bar. Denmark's TV2 reports the bottle is made of 6.6. pounds of gold and the equivalent amount of silver with a diamond-encrusted cap.
Forget the big people Olympics—this adorable baby is going home with Baby Olympic gold medals in sledding, downhill racing and more!

Teachers demonstrate in Oklahoma City, Oklahoma to demand higher wages and better classroom resources.
Tens of thousands of public school teachers are expected to rally in Kentucky and Oklahoma today.
Street performer in Venice amazes tourists as he plays the theme song from "Harry Potter" on a glass harp.
People rush into freezing cold water in East Hampton, New York, for a New Year's Day polar bear plunge.
NEW: Mega Millions jackpot rises to $521 million—just the fourth time in the game's history the jackpot has exceeded half a billion dollars.
Students staged walk outs across South Florida on Wednesday, demanding gun control legislation after last week's shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School that killed 17 students and teachers.
That's one way to get around! French ski enthusiast straps a paramotor to his back to navigate snow-covered Paris.
Gorgeous video captures a gray whale swimming through a kelp forest off the coast of Laguna Beach, California.

The New York Mets told Callie that if she got 500,000 retweets, she could take her prom photos at Citi Field. When she knocked it out of the park in only 8 days, the team gave her a very special surprise prom-posal.
Stunning lightning strikes streak across the sky over Perth, Australia amid a severe hailstorm.
THIS WEEK IN PICTURES: The 10 most incredible photographs from the past seven days.
Cyclist in Australia discovers an adorable quokka licking her bike pedal. The cyclist says she found figs on the bottom of her shoes, possibly attracting the macropod.
Fiona the Hippo pops up out of the water to say hello, before possibly saying goodbye for the year; hippos can only be outdoors at the zoo when it is above 50 degrees.
Carter Page, the Trump campaign volunteer who was monitored by the FBI after his visits to Moscow, tells @goodmorningamerica he has never spoken to Donald Trump "any time in my life."
Spencer the rescue pup shows off his incredible Jenga skills. Look at that form!
Timelapse shows a stunning sunset as snow falls around Hawaii's Mount Mauna Kea's peak.
Dramatic video shows SUV slamming into a pole due to icy conditions in Connecticut, injuring two. Parts of the Northeast will see another bout of snow through tomorrow.
Dashcam video captures moment rockslide comes tumbling down onto a highway in southwest China. Fortunately, no serious injuries were reported.
"Surf's up, boys!" Indiana thrill-seekers make the best of a flooded parking lot - by turning it into a great spot to go wakeboarding!
Timelapse video shows cars rolling through a snowy street in Washington, D.C. as the fourth nor’easter storm in recent weeks bears down on the East Coast.
Police helicopter follows a suspect involved in a car chase through two counties in Florida, before bailing out and attempting to flee on foot. He was later arrested.

"For years, Mr. Cohen has acted like he is above the law," Stormy Daniels says amid legal battle over Michael Cohen's seized materials. "He has never thought that...women, and even more, women like me, mattered. That ends now."

"The only way that I can know for sure that this gun will never hurt anyone is if it doesn't exist." Connecticut resident Amanda Meyer is the latest gun owner to destroy her weapon in support of the "one less gun" movement in the wake of the deadly school shooting in Florida.
PLEASE, MR. POSTMAN: Incredible doorbell camera captures a mailman dancing on the job in Texas. Homeowner Barbara Hickey says the moment made her day.
These ducklings think this doberman is their mother. As such, the dog jumped in the tub to join them during bathtime!
"I hope it was nothing important!" These Iowans can barely believe it when a cow makes off with their mail.
The world's last male northern white rhino, Sudan, has died after "age-related complications," according to researchers at the Ol Pejeta Conservancy in Kenya.
PLAY ON: A flute player performs during a brain surgery intended to help reduce her worsening hand tremors—and receives a huge round of applause from the doctors and nurses afterward.
You've never enjoyed anything more than this 🐄 in Switzerland enjoys being brushed!
Police in Troy, Michigan are interviewing multiple feline suspects for the position of “police cat.” The cats have to pass a background check; candidates caught with catnip need not apply!
Virgin Galactic's new spaceship climbed at supersonic speed over California's Mojave Desert on Thursday in the company's first powered flight since the fatal crash of its original rocketship in 2014.
Parents put up two baby gates to keep their daughter in her room - only to watch her pull off a daring escape anyway!

A Southwest Airlines flight departing from Salt Lake City on Monday had to turn around and make an emergency landing shortly after takeoff due to an engine malfunction, according to airport officials. Southwest Flight 604 was only in the air for a few minutes when the pilots became aware of a “performance issue” in the right-side engine and chose to turn around, according to the airline. The entire flight lasted less than than 30 minutes. Witnesses on the ground and on the aircraft told ABC News they saw flames coming from the area of the right engine. All 110 passengers and five crew members on board the Boeing 737 landed safely and emergency crews waiting on the tarmac did not need to take any action.
MARCH OF THE PENGUINS: Fans of all ages watched and waved as the Pittsburgh Zoo’s penguins waddled around and strutted their stuff at the zoo’s “Penguins on Parade” event.

HIGH-END TACO: As part of an effort to break the stereotype that Mexican food is always cheap, chef Junior Merino has added a $60 taco to the menu at his restaurant M Cantina in Dearborn, Michigan. "It is kind of like an investment. But it's a good investment." The taco includes Wagyu beef, foie gras, caviar and black truffles. Oh, and it's topped with roasted grasshoppers.
BEAR HUG: Caretaker comforts Jimbo, the 10-foot tall, 1,400-pound Kodiak bear, who needed “some extra love” after a veterinarian visit.
A long time ago in an Olympic Games far, far away: Staff at a toy store in North Carolina get into the Olympic spirit by curling with a BB-8 droid from Star Wars.

Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School senior Delaney Tarr speaks at a rally to support gun safety legislation on how she's changed in the wake of the deadly shooting at her school: "My innocence, our innocence has been taken from us."
JetBlue plane skids off taxiway at Boston's Logan Airport after reportedly hitting a patch of ice. No injuries have been reported.
ACCEPTED: Tolulola nervously logs into the Dartmouth College website to find out that she got in--and as a surprise, her mom was there to witness the special moment. Congratulations!

CLOSE CALL: Dashcam video shows a police officer falling on a slippery road and nearly being hit by a car in Hurst, Texas. Police released the video to discourage traveling in dangerous weather conditions.
Picturesque sunset on the water in Bourne, Massachusetts, where the ice is thawing a bit after last week’s "Bomb Cyclone."
Woman drives across the country and hides in back of a pickup truck to surprise her boyfriend at the U.S. Air Force Academy. His reaction is priceless

Pres. Trump welcomed the World Series champion Houston Astros to the White House on Monday after the team's "incredible victory" that Trump said was even more special following the devastation Hurricane Harvey wrought on the Texas city. "It's really a reminder why baseball is our national pastime."
Winsol, the three week old aardvark, absolutely does not want to get on the scale. We hear you, Winsol.
